## Edges

### Thinker-to-Thinker

```
from: argyris          to: edmondson            type: teacher_pupil
  note: Edmondson extends Argyris's work on defensive routines into psychological safety

from: argyris          to: schon                type: alliance
  note: Co-developed reflective practice and theory of action

from: bourdieu         to: giddens              type: rivalry
  note: Both address structure-agency; different mechanisms (habitus vs structuration)

from: bateson          to: argyris              type: chain
  note: Double bind theory directly informs Argyris's work on defensive routines

from: bateson          to: goffman              type: alliance
  note: Both study interaction patterns; Goffman operationalises micro-mechanisms of the double bind

from: illich           to: freire               type: alliance
  note: Both critique institutional education; Freire from pedagogy, Illich from institutional analysis

from: taylor           to: drucker              type: chain
  note: Drucker responds to and transcends Taylor's separation of thinking from doing

from: taylor           to: deming               type: chain
  note: Deming's systems view is a direct response to Taylor's reductionism

from: weber            to: illich               type: chain
  note: Illich's institutional critique extends Weber's iron cage to education and learning

from: weber            to: march                type: chain
  note: March's exploitation/exploration extends Weber's analysis of bureaucratic rationality

from: deming           to: westrum              type: chain
  note: Westrum extends Deming's systems thinking to organisational information flow

from: seligman         to: bandura              type: alliance
  note: Both study resilience; Seligman diagnoses helplessness, Bandura prescribes mastery experience

from: seligman         to: dweck                type: chain
  note: Dweck extends Seligman's explanatory style into growth/fixed mindset distinction

from: follett          to: heifetz              type: chain
  note: Heifetz's adaptive leadership builds on Follett's integration concept

from: goffman          to: edmondson            type: chain
  note: Edmondson's safety concept operationalises conditions for bypassing Goffman's face-work

from: drucker          to: nonaka               type: chain
  note: Nonaka extends Drucker's knowledge worker concept with the SECI model

from: kahneman         to: weick                type: alliance
  note: Both inform understanding of resistance; Kahneman explains loss aversion, Weick prescribes small wins

from: stacey           to: illich               type: alliance
  note: Both critique institutional control; Stacey from complexity, Illich from social criticism

```

